e as the library, and dynamic class loading might be problematic. It's also crucial to verify NativeImageSupport properly rather than just returning empty in case of an error. Additionally, I need to ensure that dependencies are correctly handled, especially with org.json, and that the necessary jars are available at runtime. Overall, I’m managing these complexities as I go!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining Test Parallelism**\\n\\nI’m looking into whether these two tests can run in parallel. Since the PROVISIONER is stateless and SpotlessCache is global, I’m considering how the afterEach method clears things up. It's likely that JUnit won’t allow them to run in parallel since the existing setup probably isn’t designed that way. There might also be concerns about the one-to-one mapping, especially with `Spotless_libTest`. Overall, I need to clarify if I should proceed with running the tests based on my instructions.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_HY7IQOPtM3VwhVce3JePyrJx|fc_0bf1327d49a171b60169fa0793816081a1a998777a84b24522", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\np=Path('tests/src/com.diffplug.spotless/spotless-lib/2.45.0/src/test/java/com_diffplug_spotless/spotless_lib/JsonSimpleStepInnerStateTest.java')\nfor i,l in enumerate(p.read_text().splitlines(),1):\n    if len(l)>120:\n        print(i,len(l))\nPY", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1419, "output": 1624, "cacheRead": 25600, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28643, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777993590699, "responseId": "resp_0bf1327d49a171b60169fa0777420881a1b4a6dacbdce2726f"}}
